			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Since the cloak ( not sure what you mean but I imagine its some sort of cloaking shield for guild-towns ) is time-based, normal plugins can't handle it. loop.php MUST be involved into the proccess, loop.php itself is a plugin, doesnt need default.php for that.
<br />

<br />
loop.php is the only pluginbased method in IGN to create commands/evetns that are 100% timebased without needing a user to trigger anything, and that's what this cloak thing needs as far as I know.
<br />

<br />
/tell yourbot plugin main loop to edit it ( /pluginsmain/loop.php )
<br />
then /tell yourbot plugin loop on ( i i think, don't remember, )
<br />

<br />
or just /tell yourbot plugin &lt;-- and you can turn it on/off there in the panel that shows up.
<br />

<br />
You need to build from scratch in loop.php
<br />

<br />
with full if condition for what type of traffic it is etc, the placement of loop.php coderunning is before all the proccessing of $word1,$word2 etc, to ensure whatever goes down in loop.php happends first.
<br />
Only vars existing at it's stage of proccess are $sender,$type,$incoming,$incoming_message,$args,$words,$realcase
<br />
which are the basic ones you need i think to create a time/eventbased script.
<br />

<br />
Amona<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.monkerud.com/ign.zip" target="_blank" class="postlink">Download IGN Enterprise</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
