				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">the "actual plugin" what shape does that come in? a command-trigger plugin? ex /tell yourbot cloak?
<br />

<br />
or a runtime plugin, like default.php ?
<br />

<br />
Also, if the cloak-events on the server are all socket-trackable as a $type/packet, then you don't need to put it in loop.php , but can be put in default.php who is also a none-command plugin, but it only runs every time the bot picks up any type of packet between 10-99.
<br />

<br />
If you do this, you can wrap it up as a self-installable *.pack file for people to download, assuming the "actual plugin" is ex plugins/cloak.php:
<br />

<br />
*put loop.php in your /plugin dir*
<br />

<br />
make a file in your /plugin dir called "installer" (or was it "install", i forgot) and put this code in it:
<br />

<br />
&lt;?
<br />
copy('plugins/loop.php','pluginmain/loop.php');
<br />
unlink('plugins/loop.php');
<br />
$noreply=1;
<br />
simulate($admin,"setup loop on");
<br />
$noreply=1;
<br />
send($sender,"AI Cloaking plugin has now been installed");
<br />
?&gt;
<br />

<br />
then save the file.
<br />
then
<br />
/tell yourbot pack loop.php,cloak,installer &gt; cloaktimer.pack
<br />

<br />
*the bot then wraps all the 3 files into cloaktimer.pack, which will then when fetched from ex from the central, or another URL with the command /tell yourbot get urladdress/plugins/cloaktimer.pack &lt;-- and will then unpack the 2 *.php files, and run the "installer" code at the end, moving the loop.php into the correct dir, enabling loop in the bot setup and informing the admin that the plugin is ready for use*
<br />

<br />

<br />
or just give me the name of the "actual plugin" and i can *.pack it and upload it to the central.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Amona.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.monkerud.com/ign.zip" target="_blank" class="postlink">Download IGN Enterprise</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
